ck with a continuinginitiative.}) 20... Nde3 21. Qc3 Qh7 $1 {The open lines are fatal to the whiteking.} 22. exf5 ({If} 22. Bxe3 Qh2+ 23. Kf1 ({after} 23. Kf2 Qxg3+ {either g2or e3 falls}) 23... Nxg3+ 24. Ke1 {(now going to f2 loses the queen to a forkon e4)} Bb4 $1 {(meeting the threat of mate on c7)} 25. Qxb4 Qxg2 {and Blackhas a decisive attack: one threat is mate on e2 in one move, another is matein two beginning 26...Rh1+.}) 22... Qh2+ {Frustratingly for Veinberg his kingwill be chased all the way to c4, without a moment's respite to carry out histhreat of mate on c7.} 23. Kf2 Qxg2+ 24. Kxe3 Qxg3+ 25. Ke2 Qg4+ 26. Kd3 Qxf5+27. Kc4 Rh3 28. Be3 Qe4 ({The most precise winning method was} 28... e5 $1 {(remember every attack needs the help of pawns at some point!)} 29. Kb3 Qf7+ {(stopping the mate threat on c7)} 30. Qc4 ({or} 30. Kb2 exd4 {and wins}) 30...Rxe3+ 31. Kb2 Qxc4 32. Rxc4 exd4 {and Black is three pawns up in the endgame.})29. Re1 ({White could linger on in a hopeless position with} 29. Nd2 Qxe3 30.Qxe3 Rxe3 31. Re1 {.}) 29... Qd5+ 30. Kd3 Qxb5+ 31. Kc2 Bb4 32. Na3 Qf5+ ({Thewhite queen is lost after} 32... Qf5+ 33. Qd3 Rh2+ {.}) 0-1[Event "25: Biel"][Site "?"][Date "2015.??.??"][Round "?"][White "Ulibin, M."][Black "Brkic, A."][Result "1/2-1/2"][ECO "E04"][Annotator "Neil McDonald"][PlyCount "50"][EventDate "2015.??.??"][SourceTitle "The Catalan MBM"][Source "Everyman Chess"][SourceDate "2017.08.07"]1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 dxc4 5. Nf3 Bd7 6. Ne5 Bc6 7. Nxc6 Nxc6 8.O-O Qd7 9. e3 O-O-O 10. Nd2 $1 {An important alternative to 10 Qa4 in thegames above. The knight will be much better posted on c4 than on c3. ---EXERCISE: Do you think Black should persevere with the idea of attacking onthe kingside with 10...h5 in the style of the games above, or should he try 10...e5 to counterattack in the centre? --- ANSWER:} e5 $1 {This seems anecessary change of plan.} ({After} 10... h5 11. Nxc4 {, followed by Bd2 andb2-b4,